By: Senators Kemp of the 38th, Jackson of the 41st, Jones II of the 22nd, Parent of the 44th,
Wicks of the 34th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution so as to repeal the recognition of marriage as
2 only the union of man and woman; to provide for related matters; to provide for the
3 submission of this amendment for ratification or rejection; and for other purposes.
4 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
5 SECTION 1.
6 Article I of the Constitution is amended by repealing Section IV in its entirety and enacting
7 a new Section IV to read as follows:
8 "SECTION IV.
9 MARRIAGE
10 Paragraph I. Recognition of marriage. (a) This state shall recognize as marriage any
11 union between two persons legally authorized to marry, regardless of race, gender, or
12 biological sex, who are of sound mind, who have no living spouse from a previously
13 undissolved marriage, and who are not related to their prospective spouse by blood or
14 marriage within the prohibited degrees.
